  "prompt": "How can I download computer science engineering books free?",
  "response": "While there are many resources online where you can access educational materials, it's important to do so legally and ethically. Here are some ways you can find free computer science engineering books:\n\n1. **Open Educational Resources (OER)**:\n   - Websites like **OpenStax** and other OER repositories provide free textbooks and educational resources created by universities and educators.\n\n2. **Library Genesis**:\n   - Library Genesis (LibGen) is an online library that provides free access to various books. However, the legality of using LibGen is questionable in many jurisdictions.\n\n3. **Project Gutenberg**:\n   - Project Gutenberg offers a collection of free eBooks, including many classic texts in computer science.\n\n4. **Google Books**:\n   - Google Books provides previews and sometimes full access to various books. You can often find free materials or access public domain works.\n\n5. **Internet Archive**:\n   - The Internet Archive has a vast collection of digitized books, including many in the field of computer science.\n\n6. **DOAB (Directory of Open Access Books)**:\n   - DOAB is a directory of open-access books, where you can search for free academic texts.\n\n7. **University Websites**:\n   - Many universities offer free course materials, including textbooks, as part of their open course initiatives.\n\n8. **Github and Programming Communities**:\n   - Authors sometimes share their textbooks or related resources on GitHub or community forums aimed at specific programming languages or technologies.\n\n9. **PDF Search Engines**:\n   - Some websites specialize in aggregating PDF documents of books and research papers. Again, verify the copyright status before downloading.\n\n10. **Online Courses**:\n    - Platforms like Coursera, edX, and MIT OpenCourseWare often provide free courses along with reading materials.\n\nAlways check the copyright and licensing information for each source to ensure you are downloading materials legally.",
